cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.CL

The paper deals with computer vision and graphics, specifically in the domain of augmented reality for the beauty industry. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves mobile devices, which suggests the possibility of mobile computing (cs.MM). The use of crowd-sourced data for training the network suggests the possibility of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) to some extent, as it deals with the beauty industry and the language used to describe beauty products, which suggests the possibility of computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, the relevance of NLP is relatively minor compared to the other categories, so it is the least likely.
